# Accepted / false-positive CVEs.
# Each entry is documented with location, root cause, and fix path.

# ── setuptools vendor directory (false positives) ───────────────────────────
# Trivy scans setuptools/_vendor/ and finds old copies of wheel and
# jaraco.context that setuptools bundles for its own internal use.
# These are NOT the application's runtime packages — they are private to
# setuptools and not importable by user code.
# Actual runtime versions installed: wheel 0.47.0, jaraco.context 6.1.2.
# Fix path: upgrade setuptools when a version vendors patched copies.

# CVE-2026-24049: wheel priv-esc (fixed >= 0.46.2)
# Found in: setuptools/_vendor/wheel-0.45.1.dist-info (not the runtime wheel)
CVE-2026-24049

# CVE-2026-23949: jaraco.context path traversal (fixed >= 6.1.0)
# Found in: setuptools/_vendor/jaraco.context-5.3.0.dist-info (not runtime)
CVE-2026-23949

# ── deferred major-version upgrades ─────────────────────────────────────────
# These require upstream major version bumps and are tracked for future upgrade.
# Same items are suppressed in pip-audit via --ignore-vuln in ci.yml.

# CVE-2025-62727: starlette DoS via Range header merging (fixed >= 0.49.1)
# Fix path: bump fastapi past the version that pulls starlette 0.49.1+
# Dependency chain: fastapi<0.120 → starlette 0.48.x
# pip-audit equivalent: GHSA-7f5h-v6xp-fcq8
CVE-2025-62727

# CVE-2026-34070: langchain-core path traversal in legacy load_prompt (fixed >= 1.2.22)
# Fix path: langgraph 0.6.x requires langchain-core 0.3.x; upgrade needs langgraph 2.x
# pip-audit equivalents: GHSA-qh6h-p6c9-ff54, GHSA-2g6r-c272-w58r
CVE-2026-34070
